When calling `GroupPrincipal.GetMembers()`, I'm getting the following error:

> PrincipalOperationException: Information about the domain could not be retrieved (1355).

It only happens when the code is executing on a computer which is entirely unrelated to the domain we are connected to. Not in the same domain/forest, no trust, etc.

This is something that I would expect to work, because all the other functionality in this namespace works with connections to arbitrary domains.

Steps to reproduce:

1. Set up a test domain D1 in Azure, and open up the firewall so that you can connect from your workstation (not on D1)
2. Add a Universal security group "Group1" with some members.
3. From your workstation, execute some code like the following:

```c#
